NIH Policy and Implementation
* The NIH Stem Cell Information web page lists many useful NIH websites for investigators interested in stem cell research.
http://stemcells.nih.gov
* NIH has established the NIH Stem Cell Task Force to enable and accelerate the pace of stem cell research and to seek the advice of scientific leaders in stem cell research.
http://stemcelltaskforce.nih.gov/
* A new NIH web page is available for grant applicants and research institutions interested in human embryonic stem cell research; for updated NIH Guide announcements, the Stem Cell Registry, archives of Frequently Asked Questions, and pertinent grants policy statements, see http://grants.nih.gov/grants/stem_cells.htm
* NIH Human Embryonic Stem Cell Registry currently lists all cell lines that meet the eligibility criteria for Federally funded research that are currently available for shipping.
http://escr.nih.gov
* Criteria for Federal Funding of Stem Cell Research and the Establishment of NIH Human Embryonic Stem Cell Registry.http://grants.nih.gov/grants/guide/notice-files/NOT-OD-02- 005.html
* NIH Strategies for Implementing Human Embryonic Stem Cell Research: describes the action NIH has taken to enable hES cell research to flourish. http://www.nih.gov/news/stemcell/022802implement.htm
* National Institutes of Health guidelines for research using human pluripotent stem cells (Effective August 25, 2000, 65 FR 51976) (Corrected November 21, 2000, 65 FR 69951; and partially withdrawn November 7, 2001, NOT-OD-02-007). http://www.nih.gov/news/stemcell/stemcellguidelines.htm, and http://grants.nih.gov/grants/guide/notice-files/NOT-OD-02-007.html
* Implementation issues for human embryonic stem cell research - Frequently Asked Questions (NOT-OD-02-014). http://grants.nih.gov/grants/guide/notice-files/NOT-OD-02-014.html and http://grants.nih.gov/grants/stem_cell_faqs.htm
* Federal Government Clearances for Receipt of International Shipment of Human Embryonic Stem Cells. http://grants.nih.gov/grants/guide/notice-files/NOT-OD-02-013.html
* OHRP Guidance for Investigators and Institutional Review Boards Regarding Research Involving Human Embryonic Stem Cells and Human Embryonic Germ Cells at http://ohrp.osophs.dhhs.gov/humansubjects/guidance/stemcell.pdf
* The National Institutes of Health and WiCell Research Institute, Inc., Stem Cell Research Agreement http://www.nih.gov/news/pr/sep2001/od-05.htm
