FDA Information and Regulatory Guidances
* Center for Biologics Evaluation and Research (CBER) http://www.fda.gov/cber/
* CBER Guidances / Guidelines / Points to Consider - a comprehensive listing of documents that provides information detailing CBER's regulatory approach for a various categories of biological products.
http://www.fda.gov/cber/guidelines.htm
* FDA/CBER Tissue Action Plan - details CBER's strategy for the regulation of cellular and tissue-based products.
http://www.fda.gov/cber/tiss.htm
* Cellular therapies developed from human embryonic stem cell lines initially maintained by culturing on murine feeder cell layers are considered xenotransplantation products - FDA/CBER Xenotransplantation Action Plan details a comprehensive regulatory approach for xenotransplantation regulation.
http://www.fda.gov/cber/xap/xap.htm
* Submitting an Investigational New Drug (IND) Application to FDA/CBER http://www.fda.gov/cber/ind/ind.htm
